    <h2 class="cmp-headline">What makes this different from<br><em>what's already in your bathroom.</em></h2>
    <p class="cmp-sub">You've probably tried two or three approaches to get your child brushing properly. Here's how Sonic Brush Kids is structurally different from each.</p>

    <div id="cmpCarOuter" class="cc-outer">
      <div id="cmpCarTrack" class="cc-track" style="gap: 8px; transform: translateX(-1071px);">

        <!-- Card 1: Manual Toothbrush -->
        <div class="cc-slide" style="width: 349px;">
          <div class="cc-card">
            <svg class="cc-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#2250CE" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M2 9v6M6 6v12M10 4v16M14 6v12M18 9v6"></path>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="cc-card-headline">1. Traditional Manual Toothbrush</h4>
            <p class="cc-card-body">Children aged 6-10 typically lack the motor skills to angle bristles correctly and reach every surface. Sonic Brush positions the bristles for them and covers all teeth at once.</p>
            <svg class="cc-tick" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" fill="#2250CE"></circle><path d="M8 12l3 3 5-5" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 2: Kids' Electric -->
        <div class="cc-slide" style="width: 349px;">
          <div class="cc-card">
            <svg class="cc-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#2250CE" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <circle cx="12" cy="13" r="8"></circle><path d="M12 9v4l2.5 2.5M9 2l3 3 3-3"></path>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="cc-card-headline">2. Standard Kids' Electric Toothbrush</h4>
            <p class="cc-card-body">Electric brushes clean one area at a time and still require your child to guide the head across every tooth for 2+ minutes. Sonic Brush wraps around all teeth simultaneously.</p>
            <svg class="cc-tick" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" fill="#2250CE"></circle><path d="M8 12l3 3 5-5" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 3: Timer Apps -->
        <div class="cc-slide" style="width: 349px;">
          <div class="cc-card">
            <svg class="cc-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#2250CE" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M12 2C8.5 7 6 11 6 14.5a6 6 0 0 0 12 0C18 11 15.5 7 12 2z"></path>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="cc-card-headline">3. Brushing Apps &amp; Timers</h4>
            <p class="cc-card-body">Timers extend the brushing duration but don't change how your child reaches each tooth. Consistency of technique matters more than minutes on a clock.</p>
            <svg class="cc-tick" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" fill="#2250CE"></circle><path d="M8 12l3 3 5-5" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 4: Character Brushes -->
        <div class="cc-slide" style="width: 349px;">
          <div class="cc-card">
            <svg class="cc-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#2250CE" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M8 3v6a4 4 0 0 0 8 0V3"></path><path d="M12 13v4"></path><circle cx="12" cy="19" r="2"></circle>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="cc-card-headline">4. Fun-Themed Brushes</h4>
            <p class="cc-card-body">A colorful handle makes brushing more appealing but doesn't change the bristle angle or reach back molars. The experience looks different; the cleaning limitation is the same.</p>
            <svg class="cc-tick" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" fill="#2250CE"></circle><path d="M8 12l3 3 5-5" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 5: Parental Supervision -->
        <div class="cc-slide" style="width: 349px;">
          <div class="cc-card">
            <svg class="cc-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#2250CE" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M12 2l8 3v7c0 5.5-3.5 9-8 10C7.5 21 4 17.5 4 12V5l8-3z"></path>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="cc-card-headline">5. Parental Supervision</h4>
            <p class="cc-card-body">Standing behind them correcting their grip every night works - but it turns a routine into a nightly conflict. Sonic Brush makes the technique automatic so you don't have to.</p>
            <svg class="cc-tick" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" fill="#2250CE"></circle><path d="M8 12l3 3 5-5" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 6: They'll Learn Eventually -->
        <div class="cc-slide" style="width: 349px;">
          <div class="cc-card">
            <svg class="cc-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#2250CE" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <rect x="2" y="8" width="20" height="8" rx="2"></rect><path d="M6 8V5M10 8V6M14 8V5M18 8V6"></path>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="cc-card-headline">6. Skipping the Problem</h4>
            <p class="cc-card-body">Inconsistent brushing in childhood can contribute to cavities, discomfort, and dental visits. Building a consistent daily habit early matters.</p>
            <svg class="cc-tick" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" fill="#2250CE"></circle><path d="M8 12l3 3 5-5" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg>
